<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-058-100  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 058 100.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Information Week  Feb 13 1989 n207 p30(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>First Union merges assets. (First Union Bank of Charlotte, NC)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Fillon, Mike.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>First Union Bank of Charlotte, NC, has taken advantage ofderegulation by growing from a statewide bank with $8 billion to asuperregional bank with $28 billion.andP;  The bank bought 20 banks inthe Southeast within three years, which helped it earn $283.1million in 1987.andP;  As part of its integration of the differenttelecommunications systems it had acquired, First Union choosesatellites to link all the branches to the head office.andP;  Thebank's motto is 'Common name, common systems.' The VSAT satellitelinks promise 99.6 percent reliability, which is better than the98 percent reliability offered by land-based data lines.andP;  Each 0.1percent improvement translates into 7.44 more hours per month ofATM operation time.andP;  The speed with which the system handles the500,000 transactions per day means the bank gains 120 work hoursper day.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   First Union Bank of Charlotte, North Carolina (automation).andO;Topic:     Very Small Aperture TerminalsSatellite CommunicationsBankingAutomated Teller MachinesPerformance Improvement.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotographtable.andO;Caption:   First Union's major acquisitions. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>